name: Interface UnaryOperator<T>
text:
Represents an operation on a single operand that produces a result of the
 same type as its operand.  This is a specialization of Function for
 the case where the operand and result are of the same type.

 This is a functional interface
 whose functional method is Function.apply(Object).

methods.description: Returns a unary operator that always returns its input argument.
